==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moory
<hw>Moor"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
moors; marshy; fenny; boggy; moorish.</def>
<rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As when thick mists arise from <qex>moory</qex> vales.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moory
<hw>Moor"y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of blue cloth made in
India.</def> <rj><au>Balfour (Cyc of India).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>moose</ent>⟦br⟧
